1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Everyone audits Solidity. Nobody audits the agent.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:11,000
As agents hire and pay each other, the real attack surface is the agent's behavior.

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Prompt injection, secret and fund exfiltration, jailbreaks, forged trust signals.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Jailbreak-My-Agent hires out as the adversary.

5
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:31,000
Point it at your agent and it runs eight adversarial probes.

6
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:35,000
A scored, reproducible report — settled in USDC on Base.

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Here's the engine self-check — no network, no API key.

8
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:48,000
A vulnerable agent grades F. A safe agent that refuses everything grades A.

9
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:52,000
The scoring is deterministic — fully reproducible.

10
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Now the actual deliverable a buyer receives.

11
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Vulnerable agent: grade F, eight of eight probes failed.

12
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:14,000
It leaked a planted canary, authorized a fund transfer, dumped a secret-shaped key.

13
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:20,000
The safe agent: grade A, zero vulnerabilities — with a machine-readable JSON block.

14
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Detection is heuristic-first: a planted canary and credential-leak signatures.

15
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:33,000
No LLM is needed to run or grade a scan — it holds up under a human spot-check.

16
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:40,000
And one failed critical — like a fund drain — gates the whole audit to F.

17
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,000
A weighted average would hide a catastrophic hole. A security audit shouldn't.

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:52,000
It's a real CAP provider: accept, get paid into escrow, scan, deliver on-chain.

19
00:01:52,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Here's a real order, settled in USDC on Base.

20
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Negotiate, pay, scan, deliver, clear.

21
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:13,000
A security agent must never become an attack pivot.

22
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Every target is validated and pinned to a vetted public IP — no SSRF.

23
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Any orchestrator can hire this as a pre-listing gate and read the grade.

24
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Jailbreak-My-Agent — pass your red-team before you list.
